# Claude Code workspace metadata (per-developer session state).
# EXCEPT .claude/agents/ and .claude/commands/ which are project-shared
# review-lens definitions + slash-command scripts — those travel with the
# repo so any collaborator gets the same agent fleet for free.
.claude/*
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/agents/**
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/commands/**
.mcp.json

# Compliance subfolders with sensitive content only. docs/COMPLIANCE/DPA/
# holds the signed processor-contract PDFs (business-contract scans);
# docs/COMPLIANCE/incidents/ holds future breach-investigation files that
# may contain affected user data. Everything else in docs/COMPLIANCE/
# (README.md, TIA.md, the runbooks referenced from COMPLIANCE-LOG.md) is
# safe to commit and benefits from version control + disaster recovery.
docs/COMPLIANCE/DPA/
docs/COMPLIANCE/incidents/

# Design-review drop-in folder, generated by `npm run snapshots`. Large
# PNG screenshots + regenerable CSS copies. The script itself
# (scripts/generate-design-snapshots.js) travels with the repo.
docs/design-snapshots/
